---
const steps = [
	{
		title: '1. Choose the service lane',
		copy: 'Start with the closest lane so the office can review the matter in the right context.',
	},
	{
		title: '2. Send only the core facts',
		copy: 'Most people finish in 2 to 4 minutes. The form asks for the core details, not a full memo.',
	},
	{
		title: '3. Get the right follow-up',
		copy: 'Personal injury matters are screened for fit first. Many other matters that fit move next to the $100 30-minute consultation path.',
	},
];
---

<div class="panel intake-panel">
	<p class="mini-kicker">Intake Path</p>
	<h2 class="mini-title">What happens after you submit.</h2>
	<p class="mini-copy">The office reviews new matters for fit, timing, conflicts, and urgency before the next step is offered.</p>
	<ol class="intake-steps">
		{
			steps.map((step) => (
				<li>
					<strong>{step.title}</strong>
					<span>{step.copy}</span>
				</li>
			))
		}
	</ol>
	<p class="mini-copy">Submitting intake does not create an attorney-client relationship, but it does move the matter into the review queue.</p>
</div>
